        "introduction": [
            {
                "titre": "There are times, when a colored marker light (\"beacon\") would be nice to have: when you play games with your youth group, on parties or just for some ambient light on your movie night ...",
                "sous_items": []
            },
            {
                "titre": "You can quickly make a simple one with cheap and available parts.",
                "sous_items": []
            },
            {
                "titre": "This one came to be, when we needed playground markers for our scouts group game. We needed gentle light source not to spoil the night game atmosphere, but strong enough to clearly mark the perimeter. I was surprised how well they come out and the kids were enthusiastic about them.",
                "sous_items": []
            },
            {
                "titre": "There are two main \"OH\" factors here:",
                "sous_items": []
            },
            {
                "titre": "This can't be used in (quick) motion, as it is only a tiny magnet which is holding the clip in place. For such uses fix the clip some other way.",
                "sous_items": []
            },
            {
                "titre": "What is extra suitable here is you need no tools to make it.",
                "sous_items": []
            },
            {
                "titre": "There is no switch in this design (nd adding it would complicate things), so you make - and break - this beacon every time you use it. It is quick and simple enough.",
                "sous_items": []
            },
            {
                "titre": "If you want extra effects, you can use a blinking LED (I gut some of those blinking candles to get them)",
                "sous_items": []
            },
            {
                "titre": "Picture of the finished project doesn't do it justice, it gives away nice coloured light, not a white one as in the picture.",
